article.headline: Bryant beats Merrimack 40-14
article.story: SMITHFIELD, R.I. -- Dalton Easton threw two touchdown passes and Patrick Kenney returned an interception 56 yards for another score Saturday to help Bryant beat Division II Merrimack 40-14. Bryant (2-0) held the Warriors to 69 yards rushing while amassing 403 total yards, including 123 on 16 carries by Paul Canevari, who also scored on a 3-yard run. Kenney picked off Joe Capobianco's pass late in the third quarter to make it 40-0. The Warriors dug in in the fourth, with Armond McRae scoring on 81-yard run and Capobianco adding a 1-yard TD run. Capobianco finished 12 of 22 for 181 yards passing. Easton threw a 31-yard TD pass to Jose Depadua and a 17-yard scoring strike to Taylor Barthelette, and was 10 of 15 for 116 yards passing. Depadua scored on an 18-yard run, and Ricardo McCray made it 26-0 with a 19-yard scoring run.
